<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Head small, glabrous. Mandibles short; labrum slightly incised at anterior margin; length ratio of maxillary palpomeres 0.5:2.2:2.0:2.5; length ratio of labial palpomeres 0.4:1.8:3.0. Clypeus glabrous, anterior margin slightly incised; frons with 3 grooves arranged in triangular pattern; inner sides of eyes with short pubescence; vertex slightly convex, glabrous. Antennae short, extending to base of prothorax, pubescent, 1st antennomere oblong and thick, 2nd rounded, 3rd slender, similar in length with 2nd, 4th triangular, a little longer than 3rd, serrated from 5th segment onwards, while last segment ovate, apex sharp.</paragraph>
<caption doi="10.3897/zookeys.1082.74323.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/634779" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" start="Figure 4" startId="F4">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Figure 4.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Duan, Wang &amp; Zhou" authorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Smaragdina" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Smaragdina magnipunctata" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="magnipunctata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Smaragdina magnipunctata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Duan, Wang &amp; Zhou, sp. nov. 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">A</emphasis>
habitus 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">B</emphasis>
